## 4. Dependency Map

```
TASK DEPENDENCIES & CRITICAL PATH

Core Dependency Chain:
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

START
  ├──► 1.2 Requirements Finalization (Week 2-3)
  │     └──► MUST COMPLETE BEFORE: Architecture design
  │
  ├──► 1.3 System Architecture Design (Week 3-4)
  │     └──► MUST COMPLETE BEFORE: Platform setup
  │
  ├──► 1.4 Security & Compliance (Week 4-5)
  │     └──► MUST COMPLETE BEFORE: Gate 2 approval
  │
  └──► 1.5 Integration Technical Plan (Week 5-6)
        └──► MUST COMPLETE BEFORE: Integration implementation

GATE 2: Technical & Compliance Approval (Week 8)
  ├──► Requires: Architecture + Security + DPIA approved
  │
  └──► Enables: Vendor selection + Contract signing

Vendor Contracting (Week 8-10)
  ├──► Requires: Gate 2 approval + Vendor evaluation done
  │
  └──► Enables: Development can begin

Core Platform Setup (Week 10-12)
  ├──► Requires: Vendor contract signed
  │
  └──► Enables: Customization work

Parallel Workstreams (can start simultaneously once Gate 2 approved):
  ├─ Customization & Development (Week 10-16)
  ├─ Mobile App Development (Week 12-20)
  ├─ Legacy Integration (Week 16-23)
  └─ Data Migration Planning (Week 18-24)

Testing Phases (must start after core dev complete):
  ├─ Unit & Integration Testing (Week 27-29)
  ├─ UAT (Week 28-33)
  ├─ Performance Testing (Week 30-32)
  └─ Security Penetration Testing (Week 32-34)

Launch (Week 36+ - can only start after GATE 3 approval)
  ├─ Requires: All testing passed + Security audit approved
  ├─ Requires: Staff training completed
  └─ Enables: Citizen rollout

CRITICAL PATH (Drives Overall Timeline):
Requirements → Architecture → Gate 2 → Vendor Contract → Core Dev → Integration → Testing → Gate 3 → Launch

If ANY task on critical path delays by X weeks, entire project delays by X weeks.
Highest Risk Items: Vendor performance, Integration complexity, UAT issues


RISK MITIGATIONS:
├─ 10% Schedule Contingency built in (5 weeks buffer)
├─ Parallel workstreams to maximize efficiency
├─ Early vendor engagement to reduce integration risk
└─ Regular risk reviews (bi-weekly)
```

